Nigeria has recorded 195 new Coronavirus cases, bringing the total number of confirmed cases in the country to 3145. The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control disclosed this in a tweet on Wednesday night.  

COVID-19 testing
Alet Pretorius/Gallo Images/Getty It said, “195 new cases of #COVID19; 82 in Lagos, 30 in Kano, 19 in Zamfara, 18 in Sokoto, 10 in Borno, nine in FCT, eight in Oyo, five in Kebbi, five in Gombe, four in Ogun, three in Katsina, one in Kaduna and one in Adamawa. “3145 confirmed cases of #COVID19 in Nigeria. Discharged: 534, deaths: 103.” 195 new cases of #COVID19;82-Lagos30-Kano19-Zamfara18-Sokoto10-Borno9-FCT8-Oyo5-Kebbi5-Gombe4-Ogun3-Katsina1-Kaduna1-Adamawa3145 confirmed cases of #COVID19 in NigeriaDischarged: 534Deaths: 103 pic.twitter.com/kqXEbfj66X 